@startuml Detailed Functions Flow - Data Channel Creation

title IMS-DC-SDK: Complete Function Call Flow with File Paths\n(Data Channel Creation Example)

skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam BoxPadding 10
skinparam ParticipantPadding 20
skinparam SequenceBoxBorderColor #888888

actor "User" as User
participant "Mini App\n(Vue.js)" as MiniApp
participant "DSBridge" as DSBridge
box "JavaScript API Layer" #LightBlue
    participant "JSApi" as JSApi
    participant "JsEventDispatcherFactory" as Factory
    participant "DCJsEventDispatcher" as DCDispatcher
end box
box "Use Case Layer" #LightGreen
    participant "DCMiniUseCase" as DCUseCase
end box
box "Manager Layer" #LightYellow
    participant "MiniAppManager" as AppMgr
    participant "DCManager" as DCMgr
end box
box "Service Layer" #LightCoral
    participant "DCServiceManager" as DCService
end box
box "Terminal AIDL Layer" #LightGray
    participant "IImsDataChannel" as AIDL
    participant "IImsDataChannelCallback" as Callback
end box
participant "5G Modem" as Modem

autonumber "<b>STEP 0:"

== Phase 1: User Action & JavaScript Call ==

User -> MiniApp : Click "Create DC" button
note right
  **File:** miniapp/demo/IMS_DC_Mini_app_demo_source_code/src/pages/main.vue
  **Line:** ~200-300
end note

MiniApp -> DSBridge : dsbridge.call('async', {\n  event: 'dc',\n  function: 'createAppDataChannel',\n  params: {...}\n}, callback)
note right
  **JavaScript Code:**
  event: 'dc'
  function: 'createAppDataChannel'
  params: {
    dcLabels: ["local_333_1_test"],
    DataChannelAppInfoXml: "<DataChannelAppInfo>..."
  }
end note

== Phase 2: Bridge to Native ==

DSBridge -> JSApi : async(msg, handler)
note right
  **File:** core/src/main/java/com/ct/ertclib/dc/core/miniapp/bridge/JSApi.kt
  **Function:** fun async(msg: Any, handler: CompletionHandler<String?>)
  **Line:** 48

  Parses JSON to JSRequest object
end note

== Phase 3: Event Routing ==

JSApi -> Factory : getEventDispatcher(event = 'dc')
note right
  **File:** core/src/main/java/com/ct/ertclib/dc/core/factory/JsEventDispatcherFactory.kt
  **Function:** fun getEventDispatcher(event: String)

  Routes based on event type
end note

Factory --> JSApi : Returns DCJsEventDispatcher
note right
  **File:** core/src/main/java/com/ct/ertclib/dc/core/dispatcher/js/DCJsEventDispatcher.kt
end note

JSApi -> DCDispatcher : dispatchAsyncMessage(context, request, handler)
note right
  **File:** DCJsEventDispatcher.kt
  **Function:** override fun dispatchAsyncMessage(...)
  **Line:** 36

  Routes to specific function based on request.function
end note

== Phase 4: Use Case Processing ==

DCDispatcher -> DCUseCase : createAppDataChannel(context, params, handler)
note right
  **File:** core/src/main/java/com/ct/ertclib/dc/core/usecase/miniapp/DCMiniUseCase.kt
  **Function:** override fun createAppDataChannel(...)
  **Line:** 52

  **Validations:**
  1. Check dcLabels not null
  2. Check DataChannelAppInfoXml not null
  3. Verify appId in dcLabel matches mini app
  4. Ensure dcLabel not already created
  5. Insert StreamId if missing
end note

DCUseCase -> DCUseCase : Validate Parameters
note right
  **Validation Code (Lines 58-80):**
  - params["dcLabels"] exists?
  - params["DataChannelAppInfoXml"] exists?
  - dcLabel contains correct appId?
  - dcLabel not in createDCLabelList?
end note

DCUseCase -> DCUseCase : Launch Coroutine (IO Dispatcher)
note right
  **Line:** 81-92
  scope.launch {
    withContext(Dispatchers.IO) {
      // Insert StreamId if missing
      // Call miniToParentManager.createDC()
    }
  }
end note

== Phase 5: Manager Processing ==

DCUseCase -> AppMgr : createDC(dcLabels, description)
note right
  **File:** core/src/main/java/com/ct/ertclib/dc/core/miniapp/MiniAppManager.kt
  **Interface Method:** IMiniToParentManager.createDC()
  **Actual Function:** createApplicationDataChannelsInternal(...)
  **Line:** 817
end note

AppMgr -> DCMgr : createApplicationDataChannels(\n  dcLabels, description,\n  slotId, callId, remoteNumber)
note right
  **File:** core/src/main/java/com/ct/ertclib/dc/core/manager/call/DCManager.kt
  **Function:** fun createApplicationDataChannels(...)
  **Line:** 328

  Adds CreateAdcParams to createAdcQueue
end note

== Phase 6: Queue Processing ==

DCMgr -> DCMgr : Add to createAdcQueue
note right
  **Line:** ~340
  createAdcQueue.offer(CreateAdcParams(...))

  **Queue Type:** ArrayBlockingQueue<CreateAdcParams>
  **Capacity:** 100
end note

DCMgr -> DCMgr : startCreateADCQueue() [Background Coroutine]
note right
  **Background Processing:**
  Coroutine polls queue and processes requests
  with 3-second delays between batches
end note

DCMgr -> DCMgr : Check mAdcMap cache
note right
  **Cache Key:** telecomCallId + dcLabel

  If DC exists and state is OPEN/CONNECTING:
    → Return cached DC
  Else:
    → Proceed to create new DC
end note

== Phase 7: AIDL Call to Terminal ==

DCMgr -> DCService : createImsDc(\n  labels, description,\n  slotId, callId, remoteNumber)
note right
  **File:** core/src/main/java/com/ct/ertclib/dc/core/manager/service/DCServiceManager.kt
  **Function:** fun createImsDc(...)

  Wraps AIDL interface call
end note

DCService -> AIDL : IImsDataChannelServiceController\n.createApplicationDataChannel(\n  labels, description)
note right
  **AIDL Interface:**
  com.newcalllib.datachannel.V1_0.IImsDataChannel

  Calls into terminal's modem chip implementation
end note

== Phase 8: Modem Processing ==

AIDL -> Modem : Create Data Channels
note right
  **Modem Operations:**
  1. Parse DataChannelAppInfoXml
  2. Extract DC parameters (StreamId, Direction, Priority, etc.)
  3. Negotiate with 5G network via SIP
  4. Establish WebRTC data channels
end note

Modem -> Modem : Negotiate with 5G Network
note right
  **Network Protocol:**
  - SIP INVITE/UPDATE messages
  - SDP negotiation
  - WebRTC data channel establishment
end note

== Phase 9: Callback from Modem ==

Modem -> Callback : onApplicationDataChannelResponse(\n  IImsDataChannel dc)
note right
  **AIDL Callback Interface:**
  IImsDataChannelCallback.onApplicationDataChannelResponse()

  **DC Object Contains:**
  - dcLabel: String
  - streamId: String
  - state: ImsDCStatus (OPEN/CONNECTING/CLOSED)
  - send(data, size, callback): method
  - close(): method
  - bufferedAmount(): method
end note

Callback -> DCMgr : ImsDcCallback.onApplicationDataChannelResponse(dc)
note right
  **File:** DCManager.kt
  **Inner Class:** ImsDcCallback implements IImsDataChannelCallback
  **Function:** override fun onApplicationDataChannelResponse(dc)
  **Line:** 217
end note

== Phase 10: DC Caching & Routing ==

DCMgr -> DCMgr : Cache DC in mAdcMap
note right
  **Caching Logic (Lines 220-280):**

  val adcKey = getAdcKey(telecomCallId, dcLabel)
  mAdcMap[adcKey] = dc

  Extract appId from dcLabel:
  Format: "local_[appId]_[index]_[label]"
  Example: "local_333_1_test" → appId = "333"
end note

DCMgr -> DCMgr : Determine DC Type
note right
  **DC Type Routing:**

  1. Own ADC (SDK internal use)
     → Contains "_own_"

  2. Control ADC (borrowed channel)
     → Contains "_control_"

  3. Regular ADC (for mini app)
     → Normal dcLabel format
end note

DCMgr -> AppMgr : onDataChannelCreated(\n  callId, streamId, dc)
note right
  **Listener Interface:** IDcCreateListener
  **Function:** onDataChannelCreated()

  Routes to MiniAppManager which registered as listener
end note

== Phase 11: Mini App Notification ==

AppMgr -> AppMgr : Store DC reference in openDCList
note right
  **File:** MiniAppManager.kt
  **Listener:** Implements IDcCreateListener
  **Function:** onDataChannelCreated() implementation

  Stores DC for mini app to use
end note

AppMgr -> DCUseCase : Callback via handler.complete()
note right
  Returns to DCMiniUseCase coroutine context
end note

== Phase 12: Response to JavaScript ==

DCUseCase -> DCUseCase : Build JSResponse
note right
  **File:** DCMiniUseCase.kt
  **Line:** 89

  val response = JSResponse(
    code = "0",
    msg = result.toString(),
    data = ""
  )
end note

DCUseCase -> DCDispatcher : handler.complete(JsonUtil.toJson(response))
note right
  CompletionHandler sends response back through DSBridge
end note

DCDispatcher --> JSApi : Response
JSApi --> DSBridge : Response
DSBridge -> MiniApp : callback(response)
note right
  **JavaScript Callback Receives:**
  {
    "code": "0",
    "msg": "dc1",
    "data": ""
  }
end note

== Phase 13: Ready for Use ==

MiniApp -> MiniApp : Update UI: "DC Created"
note right
  **Mini App Can Now:**
  - sendData(dcLabel, base64Data)
  - closeAppDataChannel(dcLabel)
  - getBufferedAmount(dcLabel)
  - Listen for onReceive events
end note

MiniApp -> User : Display success message

@enduml
